ENTRY            F0859   20251227   20260311   20260311       F107
SUBENT        F0859001   20251227   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                  9         19
TITLE      The level scheme of 134Cs
AUTHOR     (M.Bogdanovic,R.Brissot,G.Barreau,K.Schreckenbach,
           S.Kerr,H.G.Borner,I.A.Kondurov,Yu.E.Loginov,
           V.V.Martynov,P.A.Sushkov,H.Seyfarth,T.Von Egidy,
           P.Hungerford,H.H.Schmidt,H.J.Scheerer,A.Chalupka,
           W.Kane,G.Alaga)
INSTITUTE  (3SRBBKB,2FR ILL,4RUSLIN,2GERJUL,2GERMUN,2AUSTHV,
           1USABNL,3CROZAG)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,470,13,1987)
FACILITY   (VDGT,2GERMUN)
DETECTOR   (MWPC) A detector with 1280 wires (distance 0.5 mm) was
           used.
SAMPLE     The target consisted of 30 ug/cm2 CsF (area 1*4 mm2)
           evaporated on a 5 ug/cm2 carbon foil.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1) Error of normalization. It is not included
           into the given absolute error
           (ERR-2)  Absolute error
HISTORY    (20080131C)
           (20251227U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              19
COMMON               4          3
EN         ANG        ERR-1      EN-RSL
MEV        ADEG       PER-CENT   KEV
 12.        35.        7.         5.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           26
SUBENT        F0859002   20251227   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                  5         14
REACTION   (55-CS-133(D,P)55-CS-134,PAR,DA)
FLAG       (1.) The given excitation energies and errors result
           from fits to the three accumulated spectra of
           comparable statistical accuracy.
           (2.) Excitation energy and error
COMMENT    The recorded numbers of counts in the 0, 11,60 and
           234 keV peaks have been used to deduce the
           normalization factor k = 0.000802 (mu-b/sr)/counts
           (weighted average). Its error of 7% is not contained
           in the given absolute errors.
STATUS     (TABLE,,M.Bogdanovic+,J,NP/A,470,13,1987) Tbl.1
HISTORY    (20251227A) SD: BIB updated. DATA-ERR -> ERR-2.
            E-LVL -> E-EXC; E-ERR -> E-EXC-ERR. E-EXC values were
           adopted mostly from the first column of Table.
ENDBIB              14
